  "text": "where The resulting D(p-2)-brane is localized in η andỹ direction. However since h ′′ yμ = h ′′ yỹ = h ′′ yη = 0 there is no kinetic term forỹ so that physical interpretation of this configuration is unclear. For that reason we rather restrict ourselves to the case when τ y = 0. This is natural choice that implies that non-relativistic D(p-1)-brane wraps spatial direction only. In this case we obtain det A αβ =h yy Â ′ᾱβ τᾱ + ∂ᾱη These are standard Buscher's rules [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] for components of T-dual metric in absence of NSNS two form. As a result we obtain following action for non-relativistic D(p-2)-brane",
